# Visual feedback first

The user steers the product by **looking at the UI** and giving visual directions. They are not interested in git/branch ceremony.

## Do

- Prefer changes that are **visible on screen** (layout, spacing, sections, columns, copy placement).
- When they say **side by side**, they mean **two columns next to each other** (not stacked over/under), typically half-width each unless they say otherwise.
- After UI work: **commit + push to `main`** so deploy matches what they can see (see push-completed-work rule).

## Do not

- Leave finished visual work only on a feature branch.
- Ask them to check a branch/PR to “see” layout changes unless they explicitly want a PR workflow.
